## Passage Naming Patterns

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Location hub | `{district}` or `{district}{Building}` | `maplewood`, `dinerRubys` |
| Sub-location | `{location}{Room}` | `dinerRubysKitchen`, `fhBedroom` (fh = family home) |
| Action | `{location}_{action}` OR inside action widget | `parkWC`, `bedroomYoga` |
| Character talk | `{character}Talk{Location}` | `brotherTalkBackyard` |
| Encounter | `{event}Encounter_{Char}` | `showerEncounter_Brother` |
| Quest passage | `quest_{questId}_{stage}` | `quest_findJob_apply` |
| Work shift | `{job}Shift{Variant}` | `rubysShiftMorning` |
| System/UI | camelCase, descriptive | `welcomePage`, `settingsPage` |

## File Header Convention

Each `.twee` file starts with one or more passage headers:

```twee
:: PassageName [tag1 tag2]
content here...

:: AnotherPassage
more content...
```

Tags go in square brackets. Multiple tags space-separated.

## Where to Add New Content

| Task | Location |
|------|----------|
| New NPC | `0 - System/Init/characters/{district}/char{Name}.twee` + interaction folder |
| New location | `2 - Locations/{district}/{locationName}.twee` |
| New action at location | `4 - Actions/{district}/{location}/{action}.twee` |
| New quest | `5 - QuestSystem/Quests/{questId}/` + add to `QuestDatabase_Main.twee` |
| New dialogue | `3- Interactions/{Area}/` with `Talk{Level}` convention |
| New widget | `0 - System/Widgets/{Purpose}Widgets.twee` |
| New global var | `0 - System/Init/variables{Group}.twee` |

## Hotspot Files (High Complexity ‚Äî Edit with Care)

- `0 - System/Widgets/PhoneWidgets.twee` ‚Äî 19 widgets, has known `<</nobr>>` bugs
- `0 - System/Widgets/wardrobeWidget.twee` ‚Äî 82 if-branches
- `0 - System/Widgets/StatCalculator.twee` ‚Äî 58 if-branches
- `0 - System/Widgets/TimeWidgets.twee` ‚Äî 63 if-branches, owns schedule logic
- `5 - QuestSystem/System/QuestDatabase_Main.twee` ‚Äî all quest data, easy to break

When editing these, read the widget fully first, then change.
